{
  "tier": "T3",
  "complexity_rationale": "T3 by complexity, not blast radius. Large multi-component Rust app: four MVP capability areas, binary NAND-format parsing, trait-abstracted simulated build/flash backends, a full ratatui TUI widget/dialog/table/progress layer, new dependencies, and non-obvious design needing ADRs + detailed technical design. Graduated Security (CPU-key material storage; parsing of untrusted NAND/key-import files) and Failure-modes (safety/validation/recovery non-negotiables) stages are warranted. No blast-radius flag: all destructive operations are simulated, copy-only, real backends are no-op stubs (REQ-035/REQ-NFR-004) — no auth/authz/money/migrations/real-data-integrity risk.",
